# Isovalent Teams
# +++++++++++++++
#
# - @isovalent/backporters
#   Responsible for maintaining tools, workflows and processes for managing
#   backports.
# - @isovalent/cli:
#   Provide user experience feedback on changes to Command-Line Interfaces.
#   These owners are a stand-in for the user community to bring a user
#   perspective to the review process. Consider how information is presented,
#   consistency of flags and options.
# - @isovalent/clustermesh
#   Responsible for maintaining enterprise-specific cluster mesh features
# - @isovalent/ci-structure
#   Responsible for triaging multi-owner workflow files to identify failures
#   above a pre-defined threshold and determine a path to lowering the failure
#   rate with other teams.
# - @isovalent/cilium-agent
#   Responsible for maintaining enterprise-specific agent code
# - @isovalent/cilium-datapath
#   Responsible for maintaining enterprise-specific datapath code
# - @isovalent/cni
#   Catch-all group for enterprise code in the Cilium core
# - @isovalent/core-structure
#   A team responsible for mindfulness of isovalent/cilium codebase. If the
#   core-structure team gets added as a reviewer for a pull request, it likely
#   indicates that the pull request is directly modifying upstream files.
#   Directly modifying upstream files is strongly discouraged, especially in
#   main-ce branch, as it becomes more and more difficult to stay in sync with
#   the upstream main branch without causing conflicts. If you are not sure how
#   to avoid modifying upstream files, start a discussion in #cee-oss-codebase
#   Slack channel: https://isovalent.slack.com/archives/C05188W95GT
# - @isovalent/dns-proxy
#   Responsible for maintaining DNS Proxy HA
# - @isovalent/egress-gateway
#   Responsible for maintaining egress-gateway and egress-gateway-ha
# - @isovalent/encryption
#   Responsible for maintaining the Cilium transparent encryption related features
# - @isovalent/foundations
#   Responsible for maintaining mindful foundation of Cilium Enterprise codebase.
# - @isovalent/helm:
#   Provide input on the way that Helm can be used to configure features. These
#   owners are a stand-in for the user community to bring a user perspective to
#   the review process. Ensure that Helm changes are defined in manners that
#   will be forward-compatible for upgrade and follow best practices for
#   deployment (for example, being GitOps-friendly).
# - @isovalent/hubble
#   Responsible for maintaining enterprise Hubble products and features
# - @isovalent/metrics:
#   Provide recommendations about the types, names and labels for metrics to
#   follow best practices. This includes considering the cardinality impact of
#   metrics being added or extended.
# - @isovalent/timescape
#   Responsible for maintaining Timescape products and features
# - @isovalent/hubble-api
#   Responsible for reviewing Hubble Enterprise API changes. Enterprise
#   equivalent of @cilium/sig-hubble-api. Review all Hubble Enterprise API
#   related changes. The team ensures that API changes are backward compatible
#   or that a new API version is created for backward incompatible changes.
# - @isovalent/ignore-k8s-crd
#   An empty team to ignore reviewing some generated K8s CRD related files
#   where explicit codeownership isn't possible but the fallback to `core-structure`
#   isn't correct either (deepequal, deepcopy, ...).
# - @isovalent/infrastructure
#   Responsible for maintaining files related to cloud infrastructures.
# - @isovalent/isovalent-loadbalancer
#   Responsible for maintaining the enterprise-specific Isovalent LoadBalancer
# - @isovalent/multi-network
#   Responsible for maintaining the Cilium-native multi-network feature
# - @isovalent/networking-framework
#   Responsible for IPAM, multi-homing, loader, CNI bootstrap, platform frameworks
# - @isovalent/infrastructure
#   Responsible for maintaining CI/CD pipelines
# - @isovalent/openshift
#   Responsible for maintaining OpenShift related code and pipelines.
# - @isovalent/policy-identity-networking
#   Responsible for maintaining Cilium policy and identity subsystems.
# - @isovalent/private-networking
#   Responsible for maintaining the Isovalent Private Networking feature.
# - @isovalent/release-managers
#   Responsible for maintaining tools for managing releases.
# - @isovalent/security
#   Responsible for security related features and issues.
# - @isovalent/service-mesh
#   Responsible for maintaining service mesh or L7 proxy related features and issues.
# - @isovalent/sig-k8s:
#   Provide input on all interactions with Kubernetes, both for standard
#   resources and CRDs. Ensure best practices are followed for the coordination
#   of clusterwide state in order to minimize memory usage.
# - @isovalent/traffic-engineering
#   Responsible for maintaining features related to traffic engineering such as SRv6.
# - @isovalent/scalability-performance:
#   Maintain scalability and performance tests. Provide input on scalability
#   and performance related changes.
# - @isovalent/void
#   An empty team to indicate the lack of code owners. If the void team gets
#   added as a reviewer for a pull request, it most likely indicates that the
#   pull request is modifying enterprise-only files without a proper code owner.
#   Update CODEOWNERS file and assign proper owners. If you are not sure which
#   teams should own the files, post a Slack message in #cee-oss-codebase Slack
